parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the subframe or crossmember can cause the vehicle to become unstable, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially fatal consequences.
symptoms: Rattling or clunking noises
uneven tire wear
loose steering
vibrations while driving
and warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the control arm can cause the vehicle to lose stability, leading to accidents and potentially fatal consequences.
symptoms: Rattling or clunking noises
uneven tire wear
loose steering
vibrations while driving
and warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ball joint can cause the vehicle to lose stability, leading to accidents and potentially fatal consequences.
symptoms: Rattling or clunking noises
uneven tire wear
loose steering
vibrations while driving
and warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and potentially fatal consequences.
symptoms: Loose steering
vibrations while driving
and warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion or rust of the subframe can cause the vehicle to become unsafe to drive, leading to potential accidents or injuries. The failure of the subframe can also result in costly repairs.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit unusual noises
such as clinking or rattling sounds
when driving over bumps or turning. The subframe may be visibly corroded or rusted
with holes or cracks present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank overflow valve can cause the engine to stall, resulting in loss of power steering and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls after filling up the gas tank
often at low speeds or when idling
and the steering wheel locks up
making it difficult to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the subframe can cause loss of steering control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Rusting or corrosion of the subframe
which can lead to failure of the steering system
and in some cases
cause the vehicle to become undrivable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of power steering, increasing the risk of accidents, and can also lead to a loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
often without warning
and can occur at any speed
resulting in loss of power steering and increasing the risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission overheating and failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, decelerate, and even shut down, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The transmission warning light illuminates
the vehicle loses power
decelerates
or shuts down
and a whining or grinding noise is heard from the transmission area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and loss of power can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the vehicle loses power
the throttle actuator control module processor fails
the vehicle's speed reduces to 20-40 mph
and a warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and jerking can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The transmission slips
jerks
or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle bucks or lurches forward
and a grinding or whining noise is heard from the transmission area.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Rollover Valve/Flapper/Inlet Check Valve Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank rollover valve/flapper/inlet check valve can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of power steering and brakes, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls after filling up the gas tank
the engine sputters and bucks
the fuel pump shuts off prematurely
the fuel tank overflows
the vehicle hesitates and loses power when accelerating
the engine stalls when idling or traveling at low speeds.
